						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone set up in the Māruti temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register a gift and certain incomes made by Mūka-gāvuṇḍa, the <hi rend="italic">Mūliga</hi> of Gaṟavalūr and the eight <hi rend="italic">Hiṭṭus</hi> and others in memory of Haḷḷiya Basavanta who died in a fight. Refers to Mallidēvarasa as ruling probably the area. The inscription is damaged.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
